coach.description:
Experience

I’ve been playing pickleball for nearly four years and began coaching in September 2023. Since then, I’ve coached at multiple facilities across New York City, helping players of all ages and backgrounds develop a love for the game. Whether on the Upper East Side where I first picked up a paddle, or on courts throughout the boroughs, I bring passion and energy to every session.

 \n 

Coaching Style

My coaching style is passionate, energetic, and focused on the fundamentals. I believe in helping players build strong foundational skills while ensuring they’re having fun every step of the way. I specialize in working with “Never-Evers,” beginners, and intermediate-level players who want to grow their game in a supportive and upbeat environment.

 \n 

Certifications

• Level 1 Certified Coach – Pickleball Coaching International (PCI)

• Level 1 Certified Coach – Racket Professional Organization (RPO)

 \n 

Skill Level

skill level: 4.0+

 \n 

Additional Info

I started playing pickleball in Carl Schurz Park on Manhattan’s Upper East Side, and the journey since then has been incredible. I love being on court—whether I’m playing, teaching, or just talking pickleball. I’ve met amazing people through this sport, and I’m excited to help more players experience the same. Outside of pickleball, I’m a proud dad, husband, and avid snowboarder. If you’re looking to elevate your game and have a great time doing it, I’d love to work with you.

 \n 

Contact Info:

📧 Email: NeilDiamondNYC@gmail.com

📱 Phone: 917-520-7551

📸 Instagram: __[@Pickleball_JEWELA](https://www.instagram.com/Pickleball_JEWELA)__
